WEBVTT

00:04:29.101 --> 00:04:30.903
or where people would treat me well.

00:04:30.927 --> 00:04:33.890
I told the story in my TED talk
about going to a birthday party

00:04:33.914 --> 00:04:36.776
and coming back, and her asking me
how did they treat me,

00:04:36.800 --> 00:04:39.705
instead of asking me things that,
as a kid, you would expect,

00:04:39.729 --> 00:04:42.054
like, "Did you have fun?"
and "How was the cake?"

00:04:42.078 --> 00:04:44.061
My mother said, "How did they treat you?"

00:04:44.085 --> 00:04:45.276
I was seven years old.

00:04:45.300 --> 00:04:47.942
And I remember being
really taken aback by the comment.

00:04:47.966 --> 00:04:51.340
And she'd looked at me
with this look that I'll never forget,

00:04:51.364 --> 00:04:54.165
and she said, "They won't
always treat you well."

00:04:54.189 --> 00:04:56.697
And that's, you know,
cold water when you're a child,

00:04:56.721 --> 00:04:58.752
you don't understand what that means.

00:04:58.776 --> 00:05:01.456
And throughout my growing up,
she made it clear,